1
00:00:35,430 --> 00:00:36,700
Are you all right?

2
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:58,720
Please stay in the car.

3
00:01:15,210 --> 00:01:16,230
What is this?

4
00:01:29,150 --> 00:01:30,310
I just asked you a question.

5
00:01:33,490 --> 00:01:35,730
I guess I mistook her for someone else.

6
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:39,920
I thought it was someone I knew,
but I guess I was wrong.

7
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:50,060
Mr. Kwon.

8
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:20,360
Are you all right?

9
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,310
What did he say?

10
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,180
Why did he follow me?

11
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:33,560
He said he mistook you for someone else.

12
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:40,020
He didn't.

13
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,560
He was obviously following me.

14
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,630
- He is...
- I know.

15
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:53,610
He's the one who made your life difficult.

16
00:02:58,340 --> 00:03:00,450
That's why I didn't want
to just let him leave.

17
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,390
(Text Message)

18
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:13,930
I felt betrayed to see you happy.

19
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:17,800
Until next time, Ms. Oh.

20
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,810
Don't, Mr. Kwon.

21
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:36,550
I don't want to provoke him in any way.

22
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:41,560
I don't want to be associated with him.

23
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,470
Thank you for driving me home.

24
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:27,150
Sure.

25
00:04:55,590 --> 00:04:57,400
I'm too worried to let
you be alone tonight.

26
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:00,460
Would it be okay if I kept you company?

27
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:17,280
At first,

28
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,340
he approached me as a fan.

29
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:31,090
Mr. Lee, thank you so much.

30
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:34,630
I hear that you want Yun Seo
to be the female lead...

31
00:05:34,930 --> 00:05:37,650
in Director Han Sang Cheol's
upcoming blockbuster movie.

32
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:39,220
That's right.

33
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:42,370
I'm a fan of Yun Seo,

34
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:44,150
but that's not the only reason.

35
00:05:44,910 --> 00:05:48,010
I just feel like this movie will suit her.

36
00:05:48,010 --> 00:05:49,920
I'd be a fool not to celebrate then.

37
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:51,610
Let me pour you a glass.

38
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:58,710
- Let me pour you one too.
- Sure. It's an honor.

39
00:06:14,470 --> 00:06:15,530
Ms. Oh,

40
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:18,600
have a glass.

41
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:20,610
I'm not much of a drinker.

42
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:25,800
Go on.

43
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,910
Ms. Oh,

44
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,290
are you all right?

45
00:06:54,710 --> 00:06:56,040
Have a drink.

46
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,960
Where am I?

47
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,460
You're awake.

48
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:33,190
Why the glum face?

49
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:38,250
For me, it's been a blast.

50
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:42,290
All night,

51
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,360
I was able to watch my woman.

52
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:52,590
I should get going.

53
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,880
- Cheers, everyone.
- Cheers!

54
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,450
- Good job.
- Good job, guys.

55
00:08:01,450 --> 00:08:05,150
I've never seen a team work
this well together before.

56
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,770
Ms. Oh, the director is asking for you.

57
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:10,620
- Really?
- Right now?

58
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:12,240
- Get going then.
- Sure.

59
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:21,510
I shouldn't have followed him there.

60
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,160
Director?

61
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,980
What are you doing?

62
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:43,210
Yun Seo.

63
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:46,280
I love you.

64
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:48,690
What are you saying?

65
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:51,870
What must I do...

66
00:08:54,970 --> 00:08:56,430
to make you realize that?

67
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:02,480
Why do you seem so startled?

68
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,040
I said I love you.

69
00:09:06,310 --> 00:09:07,610
I love you, darn it!

70
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:11,310
This is the narcotics division
of Gangnam Police Department.

71
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,910
Lee Gang Joon, you are under arrest...

72
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:14,960
for the violation of...

73
00:09:14,990 --> 00:09:16,280
the Narcotic Control Act.

74
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,460
What? Yun Seo!

75
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:21,350
Hey!

76
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:24,130
- Let go of me!
- Get him out of here.

77
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:25,250
Yun Seo!

78
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,470
And just like that,
I was also accused of...

79
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:31,730
taking drugs.

80
00:09:32,270 --> 00:09:33,570
I was let go...

81
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:37,700
after the drug test came back negative,

82
00:09:39,510 --> 00:09:42,000
but just being there with him...

83
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:44,160
brought about all kinds of rumors.

84
00:09:48,190 --> 00:09:49,680
I told people my story...

85
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,530
and said he was a stalker.

86
00:09:55,830 --> 00:09:57,360
No matter how hard I tried,

87
00:09:58,330 --> 00:10:00,370
no one would believe me.

88
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:07,400
Malicious and damaging articles...

89
00:10:09,470 --> 00:10:11,480
continued to be published,

90
00:10:13,950 --> 00:10:15,990
and it was too hard to endure.

91
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:21,100
I felt like I was going to crumble,

92
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:23,070
and that's why...

93
00:10:24,490 --> 00:10:26,120
I took some time off.

94
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,790
Back then,

95
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:32,480
I was scared of him who let this happen,

96
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:38,740
of the people who turned their backs on me,

97
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,760
and of those who kept making up rumors.

98
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:46,090
I was scared of and disgusted by them all.

99
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:53,710
You don't have to say anymore.

100
00:10:54,990 --> 00:10:56,420
It's all right.

101
00:10:56,590 --> 00:10:58,050
I actually...

102
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,290
wanted to...

103
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:04,070
tell you about it someday.

104
00:11:05,230 --> 00:11:06,530
I didn't want you...

105
00:11:08,030 --> 00:11:09,910
to get the wrong idea of me.

106
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,700
Sure.

107
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,350
I don't think that at all.

108
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,990
Please stop worrying now.

109
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:53,790
You should go to sleep too.

110
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:54,930
Sure.

111
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:57,930
I will after I see you fall asleep.

112
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:01,840
All this time...

113
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,850
I haven't been able to tell
anyone my side of the story.

114
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:11,820
But now that I've told you everything,

115
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:15,610
I feel more comfortable.

116
00:12:16,630 --> 00:12:18,840
Do you remember what I told you before?

117
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:22,150
People who commit crimes should suffer.

118
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,820
The victims shouldn't suffer instead.

119
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:27,340
You should forget all your bad memories...

120
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:29,610
and become happier than anyone else.

121
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:31,600
Right.

122
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:33,800
I remember.

123
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:36,850
I will make that happen.

124
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,750
I'll make you happier than anyone.

125
00:12:42,190 --> 00:12:44,480
So, don't be afraid,

126
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,270
and let's overcome it together.

127
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:00,980
- You're up, Mr. Kwon.
- Yes.

128
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:05,670
What are you doing?

129
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:08,400
What do you think? I'm making breakfast.

130
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:12,140
You should have breakfast
before you go to work.

131
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,540
Let's see.

132
00:14:19,090 --> 00:14:21,540
I'm making doenjang stew.

133
00:14:21,830 --> 00:14:23,560
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

134
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:25,230
Do you want to taste it?

135
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:41,730
Isn't it good?

136
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,810
This place is great at
making doenjang stew, right?

137
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:47,130
Yes. This place must be
famous for its doenjang stew.

138
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:49,730
I won't spread any rumors though.

139
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:52,810
Okay. We should hurry up and eat.

140
00:14:52,890 --> 00:14:55,100
Then we'll drop by your house
so you can change...

141
00:14:55,130 --> 00:14:56,150
and we can go to work together.

142
00:14:56,690 --> 00:14:57,780
Okay.

143
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:00,380
Now, all I have to do is add tofu.

144
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:18,020
I will...overcome it.

145
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:19,710
With you, Mr. Kwon.

146
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:30,130
As you can see, I'm certain
Jung Ji Ho embezzled funds.

147
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:33,420
He's pocketing millions of dollars.

148
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,650
If you need more proof...

149
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:38,260
What about the Bujin Steel Bribe
Case I asked you to look into?

150
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,720
Sir, I can't just let
Jung Ji Ho slide like this.

151
00:15:41,010 --> 00:15:43,460
Didn't you expect this
when you put me on this case?

152
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,810
That I wouldn't give up?

153
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:46,410
Don't you know who Choi Yoon Su is?

154
00:15:47,010 --> 00:15:48,780
He was the ace of the special
prosecution department.

155
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:50,620
And he's defending Jung Ji Ho right now.

156
00:15:51,020 --> 00:15:53,600
He probably already bribed
the testifiers or witnesses.

157
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:55,980
Do you think you'll stand a chance?

158
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:59,730
Are you afraid of Choi Yoon Su...

159
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:02,020
or the person who's behind him?

160
00:16:02,590 --> 00:16:03,680
What did you say?

161
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:08,850
(Evidence Record, Jung Ji Ho,
Embezzlement of funds)

162
00:16:16,470 --> 00:16:19,130
Sir, are we really going
to end it like this?

163
00:16:19,210 --> 00:16:23,390
I don't know when, but we
will reopen this box one day.

164
00:16:23,810 --> 00:16:25,110
Let's make sure we catch him then.

165
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:29,790
What an unfortunate situation.

166
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:34,820
You still love your husband,
but you're thinking of divorce.

167
00:16:35,430 --> 00:16:36,650
What's the reason?

168
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,290
Because my husband changed.

169
00:16:41,930 --> 00:16:43,460
He used to tell me...

170
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,550
that he loved me a dozen times a day.

171
00:16:46,740 --> 00:16:48,550
But recently, he makes up
excuses that he's busy...

172
00:16:49,770 --> 00:16:51,340
and only says it twice.

173
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:54,350
He's saying it 10 times less.

174
00:16:55,550 --> 00:16:57,420
- Sorry?
- That's not it.

175
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:01,890
My husband knew me better than anyone else.

176
00:17:02,620 --> 00:17:06,030
But a few days ago, he said he
wanted to watch a drama with me...

177
00:17:06,790 --> 00:17:09,430
and bought a chicken on his way home.

178
00:17:09,430 --> 00:17:10,920
Why is that a problem?

179
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,500
We should eat one chicken per person.

180
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:17,100
When I looked at him tearing
the chicken with his teeth,

181
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:20,350
it felt like my heart was
being torn apart too.

182
00:17:21,170 --> 00:17:22,870
How could I keep living with him?

183
00:17:23,740 --> 00:17:25,070
We should part ways.

184
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:31,360
I'm sorry to tell you this,

185
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:34,960
but the reason for your divorce
isn't as serious as I thought.

186
00:17:35,290 --> 00:17:38,320
And there's not enough proof that
your husband really changed.

187
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:41,010
My husband changed!

188
00:17:42,730 --> 00:17:46,270
He's a mean man who broke my heart.

189
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:54,520
Of course, a decent man
shouldn't make a woman cry.

190
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:57,970
Here. Wipe your tears and calm down.

191
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:12,510
- Thank you.
- You can keep it.

192
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,540
All right, then. Have a good day.

193
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:28,990
Hi, Mom.

194
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:32,430
What? Tomorrow is my birthday?

195
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:34,480
What do I want as a gift?

196
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,940
It's okay.

197
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:39,050
You gave birth to a perfect son like me,

198
00:18:39,050 --> 00:18:41,090
so I should be the one buying you a gift.

199
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:44,380
Okay. I'll see you later, Mom. Bye.

200
00:18:49,090 --> 00:18:50,720
Tomorrow is his birthday?

201
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:05,970
Ms. Dan. Is something bothering you?

202
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:08,010
Well...

203
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:12,220
Actually, there is someone
who I've fallen for lately.

204
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,300
Again?

205
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:16,510
So?

206
00:19:17,050 --> 00:19:20,220
Well, tomorrow is a happy
day for that person...

207
00:19:20,220 --> 00:19:23,860
and I want to congratulate him.
What should I get him as a gift?

208
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:25,560
If it's a crush,

209
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:28,000
you should give him something simple
so he doesn't feel pressured.

210
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,980
If you like each other, do something
that can progress your relationship.

211
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:34,660
- For instance, you can buy dinner.
- The thing is...

212
00:19:35,510 --> 00:19:37,810
It seems like a crush in a way,

213
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:40,160
but maybe he likes me too.
Do you want to hear about it?

214
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:45,420
First, he appeared like a prince
when I was in a crisis...

215
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:46,710
and helped me.

216
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:50,920
Second, I said I needed something,
and he gave it to me as a gift.

217
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,940
It's okay.

218
00:19:52,620 --> 00:19:53,920
Buy me a drink someday.

219
00:19:55,060 --> 00:19:56,250
A gift?

220
00:19:56,630 --> 00:19:59,690
Maybe you're not mistaken this time.
He seems to like you too.

221
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:00,920
Really?

222
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:05,240
He seems genuinely attracted,
so just make the first move.

223
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,500
Ask him out to dinner tomorrow.

224
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:09,210
- How about a drink?
- Drink?

225
00:20:10,140 --> 00:20:13,480
He told me to buy him
a drink someday first.

226
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:16,510
That's great. You should dress
up prettier than usual...

227
00:20:16,510 --> 00:20:18,720
and make him fall for you.

228
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:22,170
But in order to look pretty,

229
00:20:22,190 --> 00:20:23,650
what do I have to wear?

230
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:25,590
I've never dressed up properly.

231
00:20:25,590 --> 00:20:27,560
Do you know what his
ideal type of woman is?

232
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:30,180
You should try to look as similar
as possible to his ideal type.

233
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:32,480
His ideal type of woman?

234
00:20:35,430 --> 00:20:37,130
An ideal type of woman?

235
00:20:49,150 --> 00:20:50,580
- Ms. Dan?
- Yes?

236
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,650
Do you have something to say?

237
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:56,180
- No. Why do you ask?
- You just looked at me.

238
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,900
That was delicious.

239
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:14,270
Since we all had a nice lunch,
today's coffee is on me.

240
00:21:14,270 --> 00:21:15,290
I'll take your orders.

241
00:21:15,870 --> 00:21:17,070
I'll have an espresso.

242
00:21:17,070 --> 00:21:19,020
- I'll have a cafe mocha.
- I'll have a latte.

243
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:21,650
- I'll have a latte too.
- I'm sorry to say this,

244
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:23,110
but I'll have a latte with an extra shot.

245
00:21:23,110 --> 00:21:25,120
I'll have a strawberry cream frappe...

246
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:26,150
with extra whipping cream.

247
00:21:26,150 --> 00:21:28,390
Ms. Oh, can you memorize all this?

248
00:21:28,390 --> 00:21:29,440
Don't you have to write it down?

249
00:21:30,350 --> 00:21:32,190
Mr. Yeon will have an espresso,

250
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:33,960
Ms. Yang will have cafe mocha,

251
00:21:34,020 --> 00:21:36,090
Hae Yeong and Jong Hwa will have lattes.

252
00:21:36,090 --> 00:21:38,170
Pil Gi will have a latte
with an extra shot.

253
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:42,140
Mr. Lee will have a strawberry cream
frappe with extra whipping cream.

254
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,700
Mr. Kwon, since you like instant coffee,

255
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:46,270
I'll go inside and make you one.

256
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,140
How did you remember all that?

257
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:51,750
I have an amazing memory.

258
00:21:52,110 --> 00:21:53,710
I'll go and get your coffee then.

259
00:21:53,710 --> 00:21:55,580
- I'll be back.
- I'll help you. Let's go.

260
00:21:55,580 --> 00:21:56,940
- Me too.
- I'll help you too.

261
00:21:58,420 --> 00:22:02,300
It's an honor to drink coffee bought
by the universe's goddess, Ms. Oh.

262
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:04,350
Doesn't Ms. Oh seem...

263
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,320
very enthusiastic and bright today?

264
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:08,350
I love it.

265
00:22:13,830 --> 00:22:15,370
